<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?mso-infoPathSolution PIVersion="1.0.0.0" href="file:///C:\ProgramData\Carisbrooke%20Shipping%20Ltd\ISM%20Dashboard\Repository\Forms\Technical%20and%20Safety\RAF%20-%20Risk%20Assessment%20Form%20v2.xsn" name="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:infopath:RAF---Risk-Assessment-Form:-myXSD-2010-09-08T18-23-10" solutionVersion="6.0.0.0" productVersion="14.0.0" ?><?mso-application progid="InfoPath.Document" versionProgid="InfoPath.Document.2"?><my:Main my:DateCreated="" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:od="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:officedata" xmlns:my="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/infopath/2003/myXSD/2010-09-08T18:23:10" xmlns:xd="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/infopath/2003" xml:lang="en-gb"><my:Details><my:Number>G 12</my:Number><my:Title>Working in a Hot or Cold Climate</my:Title></my:Details><my:Hazards><my:Hazard my:HazardId="1"><my:Description>Hypothermia</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>4</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Crew should wear appropriate warm clothing in cold weather, including hats, gloves and windproof / waterproof clothing; 
b) Food and warm drinks, but not alcohol or caffeine, should be consumed regularly; 
c) Breaks should be taken at regular intervals; 
d) Consult 'International Medical Guide for Ships'.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="2"><my:Description>Dehydration</my:Description><my:Severity>1</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>4</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>2</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Crew should increase their fluid intake - Consumption of alcohol, soft drinks and coffee should be avoided; 
b) Breaks should be taken at regular intervals; 
c) Consult 'International Medical Guide for Ships'.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>1</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="3"><my:Description>Heat stroke</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>4</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Crew to wear adequate PPE when working in warm or hot conditions e.g. E/R, Tropics, etc.; 
b) Drink plenty of water containing salt before, during and after exposure to heat; 
c) Breaks should be taken at regular intervals - Stay as little as possible in a hot, high-risk environment; 
d) Consult 'International Medical Guide for Ships'.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="4"><my:Description>Sunburn</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>4</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Crew should stay out of the sun during peak hours; 
b) Keep fully clothed at all times; 
c) Apply a sunscreen to all exposed parts of the body; 
d) Consult 'International Medical Guide for Ships'.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>2</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="5"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="6"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="7"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="8"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="9"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:Contro